    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/758</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Belgian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Van der Straten-Ponthoz</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-08">March 8,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of Your Excellency’s note of March 1 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>], 1939,
                    in regard to the discussions <pb facs="0448" n="440" xml:id="pg_440"/> of the
                    general economic and trade conditions in Belgium and the United States which
                    have taken place during the visit of Prince de Ligne. Its observations summarize
                    satisfactorily the matters that have been discussed and the general attitudes
                    expressed.</p>
                <p>It may be useful to add that the United States Department of Commerce will be
                    prepared to facilitate discussions between Belgian interests and American
                    business groups for the purpose of encouraging trade between the Belgian Congo
                    and the United States and production in the Belgian Congo of commodities which
                    might enter into such trade.</p>
                <p>The Department of State will be glad to continue discussion of these matters at
                    your convenience.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
